%N A392475 Sum of the largest parts in the partitions of n into 3 parts whose middle part is even.
%H A392475 <a href="/index/Par#part">Index entries for sequences related to partitions</a>
%H A392475 <a href="/index/Rec#order_18">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (2,-3,4,-3,2,1,-4,6,-8,6,-4,1,2,-3,4,-3,2,-1).
%F A392475 a(n) = Sum_{j=1..floor(n/3)} Sum_{k=j..floor((n-j)/2)} (n-j-k) * ((k+1) mod 2).
%F A392475 a(n) = 2*a(n-1) - 3*a(n-2) + 4*a(n-3) - 3*a(n-4) + 2*a(n-5) + a(n-6) - 4*a(n-7) + 6*a(n-8) - 8*a(n-9) + 6*a(n-10) - 4*a(n-11) + a(n-12) + 2*a(n-13) - 3*a(n-14) + 4*a(n-15) - 3*a(n-16) + 2*a(n-17) - a(n-18).
%e A392475 a(10) = 22; There are 4 partitions of 10 into 3 parts whose middle part is even: (7,2,1), (5,4,1), (6,2,2) and (4,4,2). The sum of the largest parts of these partitions is 7+5+6+4 = 22.
